2026.06.18-11.59
---------------------------------------------
Add a new rewriting rule, called "bit-to-bool Cast", for rewriting conditional expressions like "if ( <bit var> == 1 )" into "if ( <bit var> )". Also cover the opposite case "( <bit var> == 0 )" accordingly, by negating the bit with a "!" prefix.
Here is a simple example of the expected transpiling:
from this form:
    bit c;
    // ... some measurement
    if(c==1) {}
to this form:
    bit c;
    // ... some measurement
    if(c) {}
This rule should also cover cases where the bit-var is an element of an array, like:
    bit[2] mid;
    // ...;
    if ( mid[0] == 1 ) {}
